-- Financial software maker Yodlee's shares rise 43 pct in debut
-- By Anil D'Silva and Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Fri Oct 03, 2014 11:21AM EDT
-- None



Oct 3 (Reuters) - Shares of Yodlee Inc <YDLE.O>, backed by private equity firm Warburg Pincus [WP.UL], rose as much as 43 percent in their debut, valuing the provider of software to financial companies at $487.4 million.

The California-based company raised about $75 million after its initial public offering was priced at $12 per share, the mid point of its expected range of $11-$13 per share. [ID:nL2N0RX31V] Yodlee, whose major shareholders include Bank of America Corp <BAC.N>, sold all the 6.25 million shares offered.  The stock opened at $16.20 and touched a high of $17.21.